{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:psalms.106",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 106,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 106 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:1",
      "text": "Praise the Lord! O give thanks to the Lord, for he is good; for his steadfast love endures for ever!",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:2",
      "text": "Who can utter the mighty doings of the Lord, or show forth all his praise?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:3",
      "text": "Blessed are they who observe justice, who do righteousness at all times!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:4",
      "text": "Remember me, O Lord, when thou showest favor to thy people; help me when thou deliverest them;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:5",
      "text": "that I may see the prosperity of thy chosen ones, that I may rejoice in the gladness of thy nation, that I may glory with thy heritage.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:6",
      "text": "Both we and our fathers have sinned; we have committed iniquity, we have done wickedly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:7",
      "text": "Our fathers, when they were in Egypt, did not consider thy wonderful works; they did not remember the abundance of thy steadfast love, but rebelled against the Most High at the Red Sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:8",
      "text": "Yet he saved them for his name's sake, that he might make known his mighty power.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:9",
      "text": "He rebuked the Red Sea, and it became dry; and he led them through the deep as through a desert.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:10",
      "text": "So he saved them from the hand of the foe, and delivered them from the power of the enemy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:11",
      "text": "And the waters covered their adversaries; not one of them was left.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:12",
      "text": "Then they believed his words; they sang his praise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:13",
      "text": "But they soon forgot his works; they did not wait for his counsel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:14",
      "text": "But they had a wanton craving in the wilderness, and put God to the test in the desert;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:15",
      "text": "he gave them what they asked, but sent a wasting disease among them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:16",
      "text": "When men in the camp were jealous of Moses and Aaron, the holy one of the Lord,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:17",
      "text": "the earth opened and swallowed up Dathan, and covered the company of Abiram.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:18",
      "text": "Fire also broke out in their company; the flame burned up the wicked.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:19",
      "text": "They made a calf in Horeb and worshiped a molten image.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:20",
      "text": "They exchanged the glory of God for the image of an ox that eats grass.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:21",
      "text": "They forgot God, their Savior, who had done great things in Egypt,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:22",
      "text": "wondrous works in the land of Ham, and terrible things by the Red Sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:23",
      "text": "Therefore he said he would destroy them— had not Moses, his chosen one, stood in the breach before him, to turn away his wrath from destroying them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:24",
      "text": "Then they despised the pleasant land, having no faith in his promise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:25",
      "text": "They murmured in their tents, and did not obey the voice of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:26",
      "text": "Therefore he raised his hand and swore to them that he would make them fall in the wilderness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:27",
      "text": "and would disperse their descendants among the nations, scattering them over the lands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:28",
      "text": "Then they attached themselves to the Baal of Peor, and ate sacrifices offered to the dead;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:29",
      "text": "they provoked the Lord to anger with their doings, and a plague broke out among them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:30",
      "text": "Then Phinehas stood up and interposed, and the plague was stayed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:31",
      "text": "And that has been reckoned to him as righteousness from generation to generation for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:32",
      "text": "They angered him at the waters of Meribah, and it went ill with Moses on their account;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:33",
      "text": "for they made his spirit bitter, and he spoke words that were rash.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:34",
      "text": "They did not destroy the peoples, as the Lord commanded them,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:35",
      "text": "but they mingled with the nations and learned to do as they did.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:36",
      "text": "They served their idols, which became a snare to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.37",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:37",
      "text": "They sacrificed their sons and their daughters to the demons;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.38",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:38",
      "text": "they poured out innocent blood, the blood of their sons and daughters, whom they sacrificed to the idols of Canaan; and the land was polluted with blood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.39",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:39",
      "text": "Thus they became unclean by their acts, and played the harlot in their doings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.40",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:40",
      "text": "Then the anger of the Lord was kindled against his people, and he abhorred his heritage;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.41",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:41",
      "text": "he gave them into the hand of the nations, so that those who hated them ruled over them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.42",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:42",
      "text": "Their enemies oppressed them, and they were brought into subjection under their power.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.43",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:43",
      "text": "Many times he delivered them, but they were rebellious in their purposes, and were brought low through their iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.44",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:44",
      "text": "Nevertheless he regarded their distress, when he heard their cry.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.45",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:45",
      "text": "He remembered for their sake his covenant, and relented according to the abundance of his steadfast love.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.46",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:46",
      "text": "He caused them to be pitied by all those who held them captive.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.47",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:47",
      "text": "Save us, O Lord our God, and gather us from among the nations, that we may give thanks to thy holy name and glory in thy praise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.106.48",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 106,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 106:48",
      "text": "Blessed be the Lord, the God of Israel, from everlasting to everlasting! And let all the people say, “Amen!” Praise the Lord!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
